</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gobert De Quierzy was born about 1160, his father, Gérard de Chérisy III, was 32 and his mother, Agnès N..., was 27. He had at least 1 daughter with Marie N...."},"et":{"Abt 1160–":"umbes 1160–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1165–Female":"1165–Surnud","1190–1246":"1190–1246","1130–1200":"1130–1200","1135–Female":"1135–Surnud","1190":"1190","1246":"1246","1135":"1135","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","Abt 1160":"umbes 1160","1160":"1160","Abt 1190":"umbes 1190"},"fi":{"Abt 1160–":"noin 1160–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1165–Female":"1165–Kuollut","1190–1246":"1190–1246","1130–1200":"1130–1200","1135–Female":"1135–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1246":"1246","1135":"1135","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","Abt 1160":"noin 1160","1160":"1160","Abt 1190":"noin 1190"},"fr":{"Abt 1160–":"environ 1160–Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1165–Female":"1165–Décédée","1190–1246":"1190–1246","1130–1200":"1130–1200","1135–Female":"1135–Décédée","1190":"1190","1246":"1246","1135":"1135","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","Abt 1160":"environ 1160","1160":"1160","Abt 1190":"environ 1190","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Gobert De Quierzy est né environ 1160, son père, Gérard de Chérisy III, avait 32 ans et sa mère, Agnès N..., avait 27 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Marie N...."},"de":{"Abt 1160–":"um 1160–Verstorben","1160–Male":"1160–Versto